data.text: @kvanaren @chaneyj I did vote for her but yeah, she's got issues too.
@chaneyj sure, because her name is already a punch line! [ba dum tsss]
@kvanaren Ironically, the one politician who is acknowledged by name is Jill Stein.

@chaneyj Yeah I know the argument is that it makes it too much about him, or it makes the commentary more narrow, or it alienates audience. This seems so misguided, when there are also pantsuit/MAGA jokes!

@kvanaren I guess the thought process was not to give him personal attention or make it about him? But obviously it did that anyway, so ... They also don't name Hillary either, but we obviously know who Roseanne was referring to.
@chaneyj It's a political show. There is a MAGA hat hanging in the background. Ducking around the name does nothing, except turning it into a magical power a la Rumpelstiltskin or Beetlejuice.
